{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17631080","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17631080"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:22:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:22:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17347"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17347","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17347"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.13,0.11,0.05,0.68]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10037"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70038"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10037","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10037"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17347"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55500"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5325"},{"type":"tags","id":"7230"},{"type":"tags","id":"7332"},{"type":"tags","id":"7339"},{"type":"tags","id":"7342"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23498"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23501"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70038","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70038"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe intrinsic muscles of the hand are crucial for fine motor control and precise movements of the fingers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the innervation of the intrinsic muscles of the hand?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Median nerve supplies all lumbrical muscles","Ulnar nerve supplies all lumbrical and interossei muscles","Median nerve supplies all intrinsic muscles except hypothenar muscles","Ulnar nerve supplies all thenar muscles","Median nerve supplies lateral two lumbricals and most thenar muscles"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct pattern of innervation is that the \u003Cstrong\u003Emedian nerve supplies the lateral two lumbricals and most thenar muscles\u003C/strong\u003E. Specifically, the recurrent branch of the median nerve innervates the opponens pollicis, abductor pollicis brevis, and the superficial head of flexor pollicis brevis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedian nerve supplies all lumbrical muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - The median nerve only supplies the lateral two lumbricals, while the ulnar nerve supplies the medial two lumbricals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUlnar nerve supplies all lumbrical and interossei muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - While the ulnar nerve supplies all interossei muscles, it only supplies the medial two lumbricals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedian nerve supplies all intrinsic muscles except hypothenar muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - The median nerve does not supply the interossei or medial two lumbricals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUlnar nerve supplies all thenar muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - The ulnar nerve only supplies the adductor pollicis and deep head of flexor pollicis brevis in the thenar compartment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe ulnar nerve supplies all intrinsic muscles of the hand not supplied by the median nerve, including all interossei, hypothenar muscles, medial two lumbricals, adductor pollicis, and deep head of flexor pollicis brevis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The median nerve innervates the lateral two lumbricals and the thenar muscles except for adductor pollicis and deep head of flexor pollicis brevis.","The ulnar nerve innervates the medial two lumbricals, all interossei, hypothenar muscles, adductor pollicis, and deep head of flexor pollicis brevis.","The recurrent branch of the median nerve specifically supplies the thenar muscles: opponens pollicis, abductor pollicis brevis, and superficial head of flexor pollicis brevis."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","Drake R. Gray\u2019s Atlas of Anatomy. 3rd ed. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2021.","\u201cMedian nerve hand sensitive zone\u201d by Dbult is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons\u00a0Attribution-Share Alike 4.0 Unported\u00a0license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0) \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Median_nerve_hand_sensitive_zone.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55500"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17347"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21306"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21306"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/OBzB6IN9Yt8PuAAVO6TLDys6oQIKgU.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/OBzB6IN9Yt8PuAAVO6TLDys6oQIKgU.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":454}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55500","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55500"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-13T06:03:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-13T06:04:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10037"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70038"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":